    "body": "I had a need for this today. I think something like\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [74]: categories = ['a', 'b', 'c']\r\n\r\nIn [75]: codes = da.random.randint(0, 4, size=100, chunks=50)\r\n\r\nIn [76]: (dd.from_dask_array(codes)\r\n    ...:    .astype('category')\r\n    ...:    .cat.set_categories(np.arange(len(categories)))\r\n    ...:    .cat.rename_categories(categories))\r\n    ...:\r\n    ...:\r\nOut[76]:\r\nDask Series Structure:\r\nnpartitions=2\r\n0     category[known]\r\n50                ...\r\n99                ...\r\ndtype: category\r\nDask Name: cat, 10 tasks\r\n```\r\n\r\nwill work (may not be optimal though). The more awkward part is finding where to put that, since dask doesn't have a `Categorical`, so maybe just a top-level function?",
